Sentencas: A simple and cost-effective method has been developed for the fabrication of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (MT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Preparation of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly asymmetric structured electrolyte hollow fibers

Sentencas: Highly asymmetric electrolyte hollow fibers composed of a thin dense skin layer and a thick porous substrate are first prepared by a modified phase inversion/sintering technique.
Titulo: Preparation of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly asymmetric structured electrolyte hollow fibers

Sentencas: The porous substrate is then formed into the anode by deposition of a Ni catalyst via an electroless plating method inside the pores while the thin dense skin layer serves directly as the electrolyte film of the fuel cells.
Titulo: Preparation of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly asymmetric structured electrolyte hollow fibers

Sentencas: A porous cathode layer is produced on the outer surface of the Ni-deposited hollow fibers by slurry coating and subsequent sintering to form a complete micro tubular fuel cell.
Titulo: Preparation of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly asymmetric structured electrolyte hollow fibers

Sentencas: The process has been employed to fabricate yttrium stabilized zirconia (YSZ) supported Ni-YSZ|YSZ|La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) microtubular fuel cells.
Titulo: Preparation of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly asymmetric structured electrolyte hollow fibers

Sentencas: The maximum output of the resulting cells is 159.6 mW cm(-2) at 800 A degrees C when using H-2 as the fuel feed and air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Preparation of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly asymmetric structured electrolyte hollow fibers
